<subSubSection id="E03CB3956F08C55C0AE4EF479C8B4CA9" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="0C40A35D94100E8076F4324EA2C27387" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F6BEC516B83F6E4D89E74F1CF3F844E2" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">
<taxonomicName id="765BEF3F25AD5DF21AAD5698105C7461" authorityName="Nupponen 1 &amp; Sihvonen" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Scythrididae" genus="Scythris" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Scythris dividua" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dividua">
<emphasis id="D7E1A429C1465B4D360C1B601E0544EE" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Scythris dividua</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="B75DFABBEACD1F9EAEDA60D8DBF4EADC" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="S." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. medullata" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="medullata">
<emphasis id="7373A89FB5F94CB8395595787FA764AC" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">S. medullata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="2C60CC25BDEBF04451116F1D80267358" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="S." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. notorrhoa" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="notorrhoa">
<emphasis id="5E028EEBA11DD6A20C8F7EB38E499CFA" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">S. notorrhoa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are similar externally. Reliable determination can be achieved by genitalia examination (DNA barcodes not available for all these three taxa yet). Uncus pentagonal, heavily sclerotised in 
<taxonomicName id="E5BBE806C16AFDFD2179F5C3AD61F3A4" authorityName="Nupponen 1 &amp; Sihvonen" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Scythrididae" genus="Scythris" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Scythris dividua" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dividua">
<emphasis id="2BFA4077CF88DB97D05769F1DFB33827" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Scythris dividua</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; rectangular, small, less sclerotised in 
<taxonomicName id="14E625FD7F87B986E543A92E9E4463B5" authorityName=", genus combination" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Meyrick" baseAuthorityYear="1916" class="Insecta" family="Scythrididae" genus="Scythris" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Scythris medullata" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="medullata">
<emphasis id="BFB7AE3D5D35841186767716B647CF2B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Scythris medullata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; oval and heavily sclerotised in 
<taxonomicName id="E3656E593455F1B1222F338CC741EE37" authorityName=", genus combination" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Meyrick" baseAuthorityYear="1921" class="Insecta" family="Scythrididae" genus="Scythris" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Scythris notorrhoa" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="notorrhoa">
<emphasis id="152D442C61FA65ADAE2E5A84FF5571F8" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Scythris notorrhoa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Valvae narrow basally, inner margin without sclerotisations in 
<taxonomicName id="06B1F0C19CB78FD9C71EF3965B2FC21E" authorityName="Nupponen 1 &amp; Sihvonen" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Scythrididae" genus="Scythris" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Scythris dividua" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dividua">
<emphasis id="2A95B58803492B5ACD874DA1867560CC" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Scythris dividua</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; broad basally, inner margin with minute sclerotisation in 
<taxonomicName id="912453D1CA567553E196445524E71537" authorityName=", genus combination" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Meyrick" baseAuthorityYear="1916" class="Insecta" family="Scythrididae" genus="Scythris" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Scythris medullata" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="medullata">
<emphasis id="8615A24AEAE33E8F6790685BDDE4D683" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Scythris medullata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; asymmetrical, inner margin with large sclerotisations in 
<taxonomicName id="7FDF5DC17C9FF9E1E04ECDE035DFD7BD" authorityName=", genus combination" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Meyrick" baseAuthorityYear="1921" class="Insecta" family="Scythrididae" genus="Scythris" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Scythris notorrhoa" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="notorrhoa">
<emphasis id="D8689586A299F179DFB3E3A47BDE63E9" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Scythris notorrhoa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Segment VIII distinct in each three species, see illustrations.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="3C8DDCCC54FFAA30C9F7C4F98CF35C0C" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" type="description">
<paragraph id="85BB96047EBD8B22E2B95F20E9C498E9" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5B719AA1CF40E3FC1F1D9182CE5A7A04" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">The original description is quoted: &quot;Wingspan 12--15 mm ♂, ♀. Head, palpi and thorax dark bronzy-grey, somewhat sprinkled with whitish. Antennal ciliations of ♂ 1. Abdomen dark grey, in ♂ sprinkled with whitish beneath, in ♀ suffused with ochreous-whitish beneath and towards apex above. Forewings lanceolate; dark bronzy-grey, irregularly strewn with whitish scales, especially posteriorly; a cloudy white median streak from base to near termen, and a slenderer one close beneath it to beyond middle; an undefined subdorsal streak of obscure whitish irroration from base to tornus: cilia grey, mixed with white towards base. Hindwings 0.75, 4 and 5 separate; dark grey, thinly scaled anteriorly; cilia grey.&quot;</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CE6AC67182400BC2610A5A79E9A05697" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">
<emphasis id="946DB886732C8EE7285072E2FB67D18D" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">
<emphasis id="932B5FEA8A90ED07958ED093BF121C87" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Male genitalia</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Uncus pentagonal, heavily sclerotised plate. Tegumen trapezoid hood; anteriorly attached to broad transverse sclerotisation having anteriorly a rectangular extension with heavily sclerotised blunt tip. Phallus short and thick, basally more sclerotised (homology interpretation tentative, this structure could also be gnathos base). Valva short, basal rather narrow, distally broad and round. Saccus labiate, longer than valva. Sternum VIII large asymmetrical plate; basal portion rectangular with anterior apodemes, arched sclerotisation medially; posteriorly two large bifurcate processes, outer lobes distally asymmetrically extended, inner lobes with three stout apical spikes. Tergum VIII H-shaped; posterior shanks bent inwards, apices with five stout spiniform setae and bunch of thick setae; tip of anterior shanks foot-shaped.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="33E87DA5A6CC8CC4A10B2E4E090DABE3" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">
<emphasis id="BC1E760C5166978A1A5E6F4A01F6369A" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">
<emphasis id="82856561BF6F331F14E6B2762B8AA4F5" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Female genitalia</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Not dissected.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
